1
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:40,080
Riggs, Homicide.

2
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:41,880
- Nobody's dead.
- The night's young.

3
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:43,480
This is Sergeant Murtaugh.

4
00:01:43,720 --> 00:01:45,160
- Threat or a scare?
- Real thing.

5
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:46,520
He saw the device.

6
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:49,880
It's on Level 1, by the gas pumps.
I wrote the license plate number.

7
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:51,640
That's okay, sir. Thanks a lot.

8
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:53,880
- You evacuated the building?
- It's clean.

9
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,680
- Where's the bomb squad?
- Coming.

10
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:57,920
Good. It's under control. Let's go.

11
00:01:58,160 --> 00:02:00,320
I think we ought to check this out.

12
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:02,200
- Hey, Riggs.
- What?

13
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:04,360
- Bomb squad's coming.
- There's no bomb.

14
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:06,880
- How do you know?
- Because it's a full moon.

15
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:09,160
Moon, lunar, lunatics. They're everywhere.

16
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,200
- Is that Greek?
- No, Latin.

17
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:13,120
You surprise the shit out of me.

18
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:15,400
There's no bomb.
It's probably a false alarm.

19
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:18,080
It happens. He probably saw a radio
on the back seat.

20
00:02:18,320 --> 00:02:20,600
Let's not mess with it.
Wait for the bomb squad.

21
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:23,840
You're right. You sit tight,
I'll be right back.

22
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:25,440
What's the matter with you?

23
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,680
- There's a bomb in there!
- No, there's not.

24
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:29,760
- There's a bomb in there!
- There is not.

25
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,240
There's a bomb in there!

26
00:02:31,480 --> 00:02:32,720
- You know how I know?
- How?

27
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:36,120
I've got eight days till retirement
and I won't make a stupid mistake.

28
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:39,120
There is no bomb.
I'll bet vital parts of my anatomy.

29
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,040
Look.

30
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:44,040
Trust me. Okay?

31
00:02:46,920 --> 00:02:50,560
That's usually my first mistake.

32
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,840
Hey, wait. I'm coming.

33
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:54,120
Rog?

34
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:57,000
- Is your insurance paid up?
- Of course. Why?

35
00:02:57,240 --> 00:03:01,360
- There could be a bomb in here.
- Oh, God!

36
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:05,840
- I hate it when I'm right.
- Learn to trust your instincts more.

37
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:07,440
Oh, God.

38
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:11,720
The first impression
can often be the right one.

39
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:14,520
Drive shaft...

40
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:18,200
- I wonder if there's a bomb.
- Just don't touch it.

41
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:21,280
Just looking.

42
00:03:24,920 --> 00:03:30,000
What are you doing? Don't open the door!

43
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:34,280
Son of a bitch, just look at it.

44
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:37,840
That's all I'll do, just look.

45
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:41,720
There's more plastic than Cher.

46
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:43,840
I love this job. This is amateur night.

47
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:45,720
Open the door. I can't hear you.

48
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,240
Open the door.

49
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:49,800
Don't do nothing.

50
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:51,480
Not that one!

51
00:03:51,720 --> 00:03:52,920
You son of a bitch.

52
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:55,920
This is a pretty shonky job.
I think I can dismantle it.

53
00:03:56,160 --> 00:04:00,040
It looks like Beirut to me. Let's go!

54
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:05,320
Everybody's outside. Just me, you
and the cat are dumb enough to be here.

55
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:08,600
Nearly a cat-tastrophe, huh?

56
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:10,440
- Relax, Rog. Relax.
- Right.

57
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:11,680
Don't do nothing.

58
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:14,920
We've got 9 minutes and 7 seconds left.
You know what we can do?

59
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:16,440
We could drive it out.

60
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:18,360
Fine, it's your turn to drive.

61
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,760
No keys. I could hot-wire it.

62
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,160
Don't even say "hot-wire"
around this stuff!

63
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:24,200
You're right.

64
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:26,320
Why am I doing this? Why?

65
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:29,240
We're going to have to do it
the old-fashioned way.

66
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:31,000
What are you thinking?

67
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:33,480
What are you thinking?

68
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:35,960
- I'm thinking we should cut the blue wire.
- Wait!

69
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:38,600
- That's not what I think.
- You think maybe the red?

70
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:39,880
No! No!

71
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:42,160
I'm thinking it's 8 minutes and 42 seconds.

72
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:45,560
We can go upstairs, wait for
the bomb squad, and have a cappuccino.

73
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:49,240
The bomb squad never gets here on time.
And it's 8 minutes, 31 seconds.

74
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:50,280
Rog, please.

75
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:51,760
Forget the cappuccino.

76
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,960
- You know what they'll say?
- "Get the fuck out of here!"

77
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:59,200
But then they'll say: "Let's cut
the blue wire", which I'll do right now.

78
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:00,880
- Wait, wait!
- What?

79
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:02,480
How can you be so sure?

80
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:03,720
It's just a hunch.

81
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:04,760
A hunch?

82
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,720
Remember the bomb under your toilet?

83
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:09,400
- How could I forget?
- Red wire, blue wire, same thing.

84
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:12,360
This is more simplified,
but a bit more powerful.

85
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:14,280
From where I sat, I couldn't see.

86
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:16,040
Forget it. Come on, trust me.

87
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:17,160
Trust you?

88
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:21,360
Guess not. I'm cutting the red wire, okay?

89
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:23,480
What? What?

90
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:26,440
A minute ago you said blue.

91
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:27,400
I did?

92
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:29,120
You said blue.

93
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,920
- I meant red.
- Sure?

94
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:32,520
We can do it your way if you like.

95
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:34,760
- My way? I don't have...
- Quiet!

96
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:35,880
I'm sure, okay?

97
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:38,880
Ah, shit!

98
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,880
Ready?

99
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:42,640
Rog?

100
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:44,040
What?

101
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:47,000
Won't you miss all this good stuff
when you retire?

102
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:50,720
Won't you miss it a little bit?

103
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:53,880
I'm cutting the wire.

104
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:57,440
Snip. All done.

105
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:01,640
Grab the cat!

106
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:03,000
Grab the cat?

107
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:06,760
Get out of there! Take cover!

108
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:06,480
Where are they?

109
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:12,560
Bravo.

110
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:18,640
Whoops.

111
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:22,320
Right. "Whoops."

112
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:26,480
Right.

113
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:32,560
Seven days till retirement,
I'm busted down to patrolman.

114
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,920
I should've cut the red wire.

115
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:37,240
- You did.
- No, I cut the blue wire.

116
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:38,880
That's what I meant.

117
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:42,440
- We should've waited for the bomb squad.
- Must I hear this every day?

118
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:46,280
- Every day until I retire!
- That'll be a week too long.

119
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:48,880
- My feet are killing me.
- They're killing me, too.

120
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:51,480
- How?
- I have to listen to you bitch about them!

121
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:55,440
- Because you should've cut the red wire!
- I did cut the red wire!

122
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:56,440
What's this?

123
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:58,680
It's kind of soft. Not a bulletproof vest.

124
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:00,320
It won't keep anything out.

125
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,880
It'll keep my stomach in.

126
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:04,360
What have you got under there?

127
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:05,800
It's a girdle.

128
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:08,000
What?

129
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:09,880
It's a girdle.

130
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,000
Does Trish know?

131
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,520
It's a man's girdle.

132
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,040
They make girdles for men?

133
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:16,280
- Yes, they make girdles for men.
- They do?

134
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:19,000
Yeah, they do.
I haven't worn this uniform in 15 years.

135
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:21,960
- Cleaners must have shrunk it.
- You should take it to Chin.

136
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:25,720
I did take it to Chin. Look at it.
It shrunk all up in here.

137
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:27,480
I have to hold my breath.

138
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:28,680
Did you see that?

139
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:31,360
- See what?
- Jaywalker.

140
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,960
Jaywalking?

141
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:35,400
Hold it right there, pal.
Step up here, please.

142
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:36,840
- Me?
- Yes, you.

143
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:38,360
- What'd I do?
- Stand there.

144
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:41,320
Jaywalking. I saw you.
I'll have to cite you.

145
00:08:41,560 --> 00:08:43,920
Jaywalking? Oh, Jesus, come on!

146
00:08:44,160 --> 00:08:47,440
- Should I radio for backup?
- Smart-ass. Can you get the ticket book?

147
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:50,120
There are crimes in the city
and you're hassling me...

148
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:53,320
Shut up!

149
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:58,280
- Do you know how to fill one of these out?
- A long time ago.

150
00:08:58,520 --> 00:09:02,040
I can't read it. The print is too small
without my glasses.

151
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:05,240
Can we speed this up?
You may have nothing to do, but I do.

152
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:08,440
No, we can't, so will you shut up?

153
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:10,520
- Jaywalking.
- Ask for his license.

154
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:12,360
- License, for jaywalking?
- Yeah.

155
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:15,240
I don't have it on me. I wasn't driving.

156
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:17,960
I was walking.
Do I need a walking license now?

157
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,880
- Let's just shoot him!
- Is he crazy?

158
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:22,800
I'm going to drill him!
We'll make it look like suicide!

159
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:25,400
- Get out of the way!
- No, the video cameras!

160
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:27,120
I don't care! I'll drill him!

161
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:29,240
Get out of here, before he kills you!

162
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:31,880
- Go that way! Not that way!
- This way! Over here!

163
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,000
- Run!
- Now!

164
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:36,080
Run!

165
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:46,520
Wait a minute!

166
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:49,760
You forgot to sign.

167
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,280
What was that?

168
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:55,200
Wait a minute.
You forgot to sign the form.

169
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:56,280
Who are you?

170
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:57,760
You're not the regular guy?

171
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,280
- He's on vacation.
- On vacation?

172
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:02,680
Well, who the hell is that?

173
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:05,800
Get in the truck.

174
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:14,640
You fucking prick!

175
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:22,000
Are you a cop?

176
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:25,080
Fourteen-sixty. Into pursuit.
Will continue transmission.

177
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,200
Call 911.

178
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:29,320
Okay, honey. Let me drive.
We're in pursuit.

179
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:32,880
I'm driving! Don't worry.

180
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:40,920
This fool picked the wrong time
to mess with the wrong lady.

181
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:44,080
Just stay close.

182
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:50,640
Right behind you, baby!

183
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:52,000
Take a good look!

184
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:56,600
Delores the Road Warrior
is dead on your raggedy ass!

185
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:06,240
Ram him!

186
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:13,520
- Watch out, Riggs!
- Come on!

187
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:22,600
Are you married, sugar?

188
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:24,640
What? Yes, 24 years. 24 years!

189
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:27,760
Yeah, but is it working?

190
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:36,080
- You can't get closer?
- I am. I'm getting closer.

191
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:39,520
Hold on, Riggs!

192
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:49,800
Hold on! We got you!

193
00:11:50,040 --> 00:11:52,000
Hold on!

194
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:54,120
- I told you I could do it!
- Closer!

195
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:56,080
- Get me up there!
- Go!

196
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:58,920
I am!

197
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:05,040
Back off!

198
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:16,880
If he falls, don't hit him.

199
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:20,640
Don't worry, I've got something for you.

200
00:12:56,360 --> 00:13:00,800
Thanks for the interest, sugar,
but one thing at a time.

201
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:16,080
- Catch him!
- All right!

202
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:20,880
Keep singing. Just stay close.

203
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:28,000
Relax, baby. Relax.

204
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:30,120
Keep your hands off my thighs!

205
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:34,160
- He's in trouble. Watch out!
- I got him!

206
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:46,680
I'm getting too old for this.

207
00:13:46,920 --> 00:13:50,320
Not for me, you're not, sugar.

208
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:54,760
You have the right to remain unconscious.

209
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:58,880
Anything you say ain't gonna be much.

210
00:14:01,360 --> 00:14:03,000
Hey, Riggs. Are you all right?

211
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:07,080
I'm okay. I think we've got to book
this guy for not wearing his seat belt.

212
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:09,080
That was dynamite driving.

213
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:13,160
- She's a dynamite driver.
- I'll show you dynamite.

214
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:15,880
Sho 'nuff!

215
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,880
What have you two been up to?

216
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:19,840
What do you mean? We were in pursuit.

217
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:22,000
- I saw you kiss her.
- I didn't. She kissed me.

218
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:25,080
It looked mutual to me.
Wipe that lipstick off...

219
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:28,800
Hey, go spit, Riggs.

220
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:30,120
Are you okay?

221
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:31,960
Are you all right?

222
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:34,160
Back to bed. Back to bed.

223
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,440
Good morning, guys. Daddy.

224
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:40,320
How about treating your dad
to breakfast today?

225
00:14:40,560 --> 00:14:44,920
- You've got six more days to go.
- Laundry service.

226
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:46,360
Hold this. Hangers?

227
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:49,800
I'm springing for the soap.
Nothing too fancy. Cute dog.

228
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:51,560
It's a Westie.

229
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:53,400
'Morning, Trish.

230
00:14:53,640 --> 00:14:55,360
'Morning, Rog.

231
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:57,120
- Good morning, Nick.
- Spare me.

232
00:14:57,360 --> 00:14:59,800
- What, you didn't brush your teeth?
- Hold it, mister.

233
00:15:00,040 --> 00:15:01,720
Just looking for some orange juice.

234
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:05,440
Don't get any fingerprints on the door
and put the glass in the dishwasher.

235
00:15:05,680 --> 00:15:07,160
Did somebody commit a murder?

236
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:09,000
Someone's coming to see the house.

237
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:12,440
A little mess adds to the charm.

238
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:23,000
How's this?

239
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:26,040
Isn't this great? Okay?

240
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:27,480
Kelly's Pool Hall.

241
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:30,440
Right, Kelly, hi. Let me speak to Dad.

242
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:34,360
Hi, honey. How are you?
I thought I asked you not to call me here.

243
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,960
- It's for you.
- Me?

244
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,560
Who is it? Hello?

245
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:44,280
{y:i}Hi. It's my first day at work. Are you
{y:i}going to come by and wish me luck?

246
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:47,480
- Beautiful, huh? Come on, check it out.
- Beautiful lawn.

247
00:15:47,720 --> 00:15:48,840
It's great.

248
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:51,040
See how quiet it is here? Listen.

249
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:52,680
Isn't that great? Come on.

250
00:15:52,920 --> 00:15:54,840
- It's quiet.
- The inside's even better.

251
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:59,600
- It's the people to look at the house.
- And our broker.

252
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:02,880
Just want to make sure.

253
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:07,200
I'll show you this room first.
It's my favorite.

254
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:09,040
Is that it? Does that say it all?

255
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:10,120
It's very nice.

256
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:13,120
I love that picture window.

257
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:15,640
- It's just been completely replaced.
- Why?

258
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:18,760
A drug dealer came through with his car
and crashed right in.

259
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,480
Shot up the whole place.

260
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:24,760
Son of a bitch!
I'm going to cut him off at the knees.

261
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:28,160
It's true. It's true. True.
Okay, anyway, look.

262
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:30,680
Do you like the drapes?
Maybe she'll leave them.

263
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:32,600
- I thought you quit.
- I did.

264
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:36,360
- You'll stink up the house. Don't smoke.
- I'm itching to.

265
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,280
Here.

266
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:39,880
Chew on these.

267
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:43,800
I have to tell you this. It's the law.
It's called "full disclosure".

268
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:47,400
Anything else you want to disclose
before we go on?

269
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:50,840
Now that you mention it, the bathroom
has been completely remodeled...

270
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,720
...due to unexpected bomb damage.

271
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:54,280
Hey, come on. It's okay.

272
00:16:54,520 --> 00:16:55,800
Son of a bitch!

273
00:16:56,040 --> 00:17:00,080
Don't, don't. You'll never sell the house.

274
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:06,440
Okay. We saw enough of the kitchen.
I'll show you the upstairs.

275
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:10,920
Wait till you see it.
It's beautiful. You'll love it.

276
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:17,200
They're gone. Leo Getz,
I'm going to kill him.

277
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:19,640
Son of a bitch. I'm going to kill him!

278
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:23,280
You have to let me, Riggs!

279
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:25,400
They weren't going to buy it anyway!

280
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:28,560
- You scared them away!
- They couldn't afford to buy it!

281
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:31,080
- Oh, I see.
- Okay, relax.

282
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:34,520
I had to tell them everything.
It's the law. "Full disclosure."

283
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:37,720
- You must have heard of it?
- I'm a cop. I'm the law!

284
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:41,480
- Get off me! What is it with you?
- Hold it!

285
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:42,720
Okay, okay.

286
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:46,800
At least he didn't tell them
about the nail-gun incident.

287
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:50,040
I forgot. Did you have a permit
when you built over the garage?

288
00:17:50,280 --> 00:17:51,240
Permit?

289
00:17:51,480 --> 00:17:53,760
Hold it! Leo's here. I'll take care of it.

290
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:56,840
I'll make some calls.
We'll get some back-dated permits.

291
00:17:57,080 --> 00:18:00,960
- Which phone can I use?
- Sunroom.

292
00:18:02,040 --> 00:18:04,520
- It must be easier than this.
- Count on Leo Getz.

293
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:07,960
You need less aggravation.
Come to work with me.

294
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:11,800
Thank you, Leo! Son of a bitch.

295
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:26,520
Did you forget something?

296
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:31,560
This.

297
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:33,880
You wear it. You sleep in it. You eat in it.

298
00:18:34,120 --> 00:18:34,760
Okay?

299
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:36,920
Six more days.

300
00:18:37,160 --> 00:18:38,200
And you...

301
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:40,240
...keep an eye on him.

302
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:42,640
Sure.

303
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:47,960
She loves me.

304
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:50,400
Stop fronting yourself.
You know what I'm saying?

305
00:18:50,640 --> 00:18:54,000
Swing with me and my crew.

306
00:18:56,800 --> 00:19:00,000
- I got school.
- Forget school.

307
00:19:01,360 --> 00:19:03,960
Here comes your pops.

308
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:06,880
- Later.
- All right, gotcha.

309
00:19:07,120 --> 00:19:10,160
Next time.

310
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:15,200
- 'Morning, Rog.
- How are you doing?

311
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:17,600
Hey, Nick?

312
00:19:17,840 --> 00:19:19,400
- Wasn't that Darryl?
- Yeah.

313
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:22,240
I haven't seen him around in a while.

314
00:19:22,480 --> 00:19:23,920
He dropped out of high school.

315
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:26,120
Those are pretty gang colors he's wearing.

316
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:28,680
Yeah, I know.

317
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:30,800
Hey, Nick?

318
00:19:31,040 --> 00:19:31,960
Yeah, Dad?

319
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:33,800
Be good.

320
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:36,400
Word.

321
00:19:37,560 --> 00:19:39,000
"Word", Nick.

322
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:41,840
Word.

323
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:44,360
"Word", Riggs.

324
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:46,160
"Word", Rog.

325
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:48,000
- What are we talking about?
- "Word."

326
00:19:48,240 --> 00:19:51,280
Four letters. Starts with a "W",
"O" in the middle, "D" at the end.

327
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:53,640
Oh, yeah, that word.

328
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:56,320
"Word."

329
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:10,680
- Tyrone, my man, how are you?
- Jack, how's it going?

330
00:20:10,920 --> 00:20:12,880
- Let's take a walk.
- Wait here for me.

331
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:15,640
Look around. This is my dream
and it's all coming true.

332
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:20,240
You sank your money into this,
out here in the middle of the desert?

333
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:22,680
- Know why it'll be a gold mine?
- Do tell.

334
00:20:22,920 --> 00:20:26,440
Because no one wants to live
next door to a menace like you.

335
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:29,680
I came to do business,
not to be insulted by you.

336
00:20:29,920 --> 00:20:31,280
Relax, Tyrone.

337
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:34,000
Like houses,
friendships need strong foundations.

338
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:38,080
Smitty, come here. Come here.

339
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:42,080
What's wrong with you?
Don't I pay you good and take care of you?

340
00:20:42,320 --> 00:20:45,560
- Sure you do.
- What about the stunt you and Billy pulled?

341
00:20:45,800 --> 00:20:48,760
- It was a good plan. It worked.
- It worked? It didn't work.

342
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,520
You got nailed, first time out.

343
00:20:50,760 --> 00:20:53,440
Nobody who works for me
goes into business for themselves.

344
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:56,480
Do you understand me?
See how that can jeopardize everything?

345
00:20:56,720 --> 00:20:58,840
- Right?
- Whatever.

346
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:01,560
Especially trying to pop an armored car.

347
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:05,120
Okay, Billy got caught.
There's nothing I can do about that now.

348
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:07,800
He'll have to face the music on his own.

349
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:09,520
But you and me...

350
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:11,120
...we're gonna start over.

351
00:21:11,360 --> 00:21:13,680
You know what I mean?

352
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:15,640
- Whatever you say.
- Good.

353
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:19,800
Glad you understand
what I'm talking about.

354
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:28,120
Now we've got a relationship
we can build on.

355
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:31,800
- Employee problems. You know how it is?
- Yeah, right.

356
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:34,360
You invest time and energy
into training somebody.

357
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:38,080
Then they get greedy and do something
stupid that jeopardizes everything.

358
00:21:38,320 --> 00:21:39,360
It's a bitch!

359
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:41,640
Stick around. This is the good part.

360
00:21:41,880 --> 00:21:44,960
We can put our initials in there.

361
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:48,040
Jesus Christ!

362
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:52,440
Lankershim and Vineland.
Where are we going?

363
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:56,160
Right here. Rianne's got a new job.
I promised her I'd stop by.

364
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:58,520
That's a good reason.

365
00:21:58,760 --> 00:22:02,800
All right. Here we are.

366
00:22:07,240 --> 00:22:10,240
- You got any silver, any change?
- We're cops.

367
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:15,280
That's right, we're cops. Not crooks.
I'll get change.

368
00:22:23,120 --> 00:22:26,320
Get down! All of you!

369
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:31,400
Get down!

370
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:47,280
How do you like me?

371
00:22:47,520 --> 00:22:49,720
What are you doing with a rubber gun?

372
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:51,080
This is a film.

373
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:54,200
Cut, cut! Who the fuck is this lunatic?

374
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:56,800
- Get him off my set.
- This isn't part of the story.

375
00:22:57,040 --> 00:23:00,320
- Where did you come from?
- Can we get a cop on set?

376
00:23:00,560 --> 00:23:03,640
Rianne, I'm so sorry.
I feel like a microbe right now.

377
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:06,520
- You really thought I was in trouble?
- I did.

378
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:09,280
A real cop. Go sit in your fucking trailer.

379
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:11,600
- Are you a fucking idiot?
- I apologize.

380
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:14,920
He's a friend of mine, a policeman.
He thought I was in trouble.

381
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:16,160
We're both...

382
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:17,600
He's a friend of yours?

383
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:20,880
Let me tell you something:
You're fired. Have a nice day.

384
00:23:21,120 --> 00:23:23,440
Fired? Riggs, what'd you do?

385
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:24,800
You're not fired.

386
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:27,160
No, you're not. Just take it easy.

387
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:29,400
You can't fire her for something I did.

388
00:23:29,640 --> 00:23:31,720
I don't care whose mistake it was.
She's fired.

389
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:33,160
I apologize to everyone.

390
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:34,400
Don't push him!

391
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:35,760
All of you, go!

392
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,680
Just take it easy. Don't push him.

393
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:40,960
Get off my set, all right?
What are you, deaf?

394
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,000
Get off my set!

395
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:44,440
On any normal day,
I'd smack you in the mouth.

396
00:23:44,680 --> 00:23:45,480
Is that so?

397
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:46,360
Don't!

398
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:48,280
It's a normal day.

399
00:23:48,520 --> 00:23:51,120
I'm sorry. Listen, are you okay? I'm sorry.

400
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:54,440
I'm all thumbs. He fell down.
Let me help you.

401
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:56,080
I said don't hit him!

402
00:23:56,320 --> 00:23:58,040
- Is she fired?
- Yes, she's fired.

403
00:23:58,280 --> 00:23:59,400
- Is she fired?
- No, no.

404
00:23:59,640 --> 00:24:01,240
- It's okay.
- Does she get a raise?

405
00:24:01,480 --> 00:24:03,480
- Yes. I said, "yes".
- Good.

406
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:07,200
Rianne, I think you have a new friend here.

407
00:24:07,440 --> 00:24:10,800
We'd like you to come back.

408
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:15,800
You can't settle every problem
with your fists.

409
00:24:16,040 --> 00:24:18,920
- I couldn't use my gun with that crowd.
- Six more days.

410
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:20,720
I don't want to hear that anymore.

411
00:24:20,960 --> 00:24:23,520
Did Rianne get her job back?
Did she get a raise?

412
00:24:23,760 --> 00:24:25,560
I don't hear a "thank you".

413
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:29,720
Maybe I should become a Hollywood agent.
What do you think?

414
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:31,560
- It won't work.
- Why?

415
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:33,720
You don't have that killer instinct.

416
00:24:33,960 --> 00:24:35,800
Son of a bitch!

417
00:24:36,040 --> 00:24:39,920
- We should've put a bag on the meter.
- I'll put it in the glove compartment.

418
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:41,520
I don't do that anymore.

419
00:24:41,760 --> 00:24:43,000
Oh, yeah? Good man.

420
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:46,840
It's full. Put it in the back seat.

421
00:24:49,160 --> 00:24:53,720
- You really like those things?
- These? They're good.

422
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:59,120
You can eat a box of them
and still be dying for a cigarette.

423
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:04,000
- Did you cut yourself shaving?
- Yeah.

424
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:05,880
Old razor?

425
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:08,760
Old face.

426
00:25:09,320 --> 00:25:12,840
You're letting this retirement thing
get you down.

427
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:15,800
Spend a few more years
getting used to the idea. Why quit?

428
00:25:16,040 --> 00:25:18,600
- I've got plans for my retirement.
- Oh, yeah, plans.

429
00:25:18,840 --> 00:25:20,400
- I do. Big plans.
- Big plans?

430
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:22,640
- I've had them for a long time.
- Like what?

431
00:25:22,880 --> 00:25:25,240
Like...

432
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:27,680
- Things, man.
- Things.

433
00:25:27,920 --> 00:25:28,720
Things.

434
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:30,480
Things I've put off for too long.

435
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:33,440
Oh, those things. I've got those, too.

436
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:37,520
I see you've given this a lot of thought.

437
00:25:38,520 --> 00:25:40,360
Yeah.

438
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:44,080
I've given it a lot of thought.

439
00:26:01,040 --> 00:26:02,520
Goddamn it!

440
00:26:02,760 --> 00:26:05,680
- What's going on?
- I'm pissed off. You need a reason?

441
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:09,560
- I thought I heard gunfire.
- Get your hearing checked! Put that away!

442
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:10,960
What are you looking at?

443
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:14,200
Hey, man. Peace.

444
00:26:34,120 --> 00:26:37,680
Why'd you call us down here?

445
00:26:38,440 --> 00:26:39,640
How are you doing, son?

446
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:43,600
Does your mother know you're here?

447
00:26:45,640 --> 00:26:47,800
- Did you do this?
- Nice shooting.

448
00:26:48,040 --> 00:26:50,040
Better than Billy the Kid.

449
00:26:50,280 --> 00:26:52,080
Diaper rash makes you cranky, huh?

450
00:26:52,320 --> 00:26:55,240
Give it to your mom.
Maybe she'll stick it on the refrigerator.

451
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:57,360
- Can I borrow your glasses?
- Yeah.

452
00:26:57,600 --> 00:26:58,600
Who's wearing?

453
00:26:58,840 --> 00:27:00,000
Roger, you are.

454
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:01,920
Why me? You guys should be wearing.

455
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:03,680
Mr. Murtaugh, let me assist you.

456
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:06,680
I don't need help.
I've been dressing myself since I was 30.

457
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:08,920
- Okay, man, just trying to help.
- Get back.

458
00:27:09,160 --> 00:27:10,720
All you perverts, turn your heads.

459
00:27:10,960 --> 00:27:14,360
- Take it off, baby.
- Hold this shirt.

460
00:27:14,520 --> 00:27:16,120
You're wearing a girdle.

461
00:27:16,360 --> 00:27:18,360
- He's got a girdle.
- This is not a girdle.

462
00:27:18,600 --> 00:27:20,280
This is not a girdle. It's my back.

463
00:27:20,520 --> 00:27:23,240
My back went out on me.

464
00:27:23,320 --> 00:27:27,080
I hurt my back this morning lifting weights.
What are you talking about?

465
00:27:27,320 --> 00:27:28,440
I saw him do it.

466
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:29,960
Everybody, listen up.

467
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:32,840
I want you all to look at these.
Lovely bullets.

468
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:33,640
Cute.

469
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:38,760
Notice the smooth jacket.
Pay particular attention to the tip.

470
00:27:41,800 --> 00:27:46,880
Now, you've all seen these vests stop
a.357 Magnum bullet.

471
00:27:49,520 --> 00:27:52,360
Observe.

472
00:28:05,040 --> 00:28:07,760
Son of a bitch.

473
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:12,160
- Armor-piercing bullets?
- Yeah, cop killers.

474
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:16,080
Those bullets came from the gun
of a suspect we arrested yesterday.

475
00:28:16,320 --> 00:28:18,160
They're out there on the streets.

476
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:21,400
Vests are optional, boys and girls.
Especially boys.

477
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:24,400
See you, Riggs.

478
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:28,240
Cop killers.

479
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:31,960
Son of a bitch.

480
00:28:32,960 --> 00:28:38,760
I think we should talk to Billy Phelps.
I'll have him brought in for interrogation.

481
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:47,800
I'm here to talk to Billy Phelps.

482
00:28:48,040 --> 00:28:50,680
- Can I see your ID, please?
- Sure.

483
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:54,120
William Phelps, armored car suspect.
He's been moved to Interrogation.

484
00:28:54,360 --> 00:28:58,680
- Do you know where that is?
- Sure. I've been there a lot.

485
00:29:06,320 --> 00:29:09,360
Same floor.

486
00:29:09,640 --> 00:29:14,640
I guess now you're retiring, that Swiss
bank account will come in pretty handy.

487
00:29:14,880 --> 00:29:17,440
How much you got in there, $1 million?
$1.5 million?

488
00:29:17,680 --> 00:29:19,320
- $5 million.
- $5 million?

489
00:29:19,560 --> 00:29:21,240
Well, you deserve it.

490
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:25,840
It's better than those
miserable drug dealers getting it.

491
00:29:28,280 --> 00:29:30,080
What are you talking about?

492
00:29:30,320 --> 00:29:34,040
Don't sweat it. You laundered it,
didn't you? They can't trace it.

493
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:35,920
- They can't trace it.
- What?

494
00:29:36,160 --> 00:29:39,200
So long as I get an invite
to "casa de" Murtaugh, I'm happy.

495
00:29:39,440 --> 00:29:40,440
"Casa" what?

496
00:29:40,680 --> 00:29:42,840
- I've never been to Portugal.
- Stop joking.

497
00:29:43,080 --> 00:29:43,960
She's a cop.

498
00:29:44,200 --> 00:29:47,920
I know she's a cop.
She's probably on the take, too.

499
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:49,880
The whole Force is bent.

500
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:52,600
She may be wearing a skirt,
but we're all brothers.

501
00:29:52,840 --> 00:29:56,040
You know I have nothing.
I ain't been to Portugal.

502
00:29:56,280 --> 00:29:59,760
Listen to me.

503
00:30:01,160 --> 00:30:03,440
Son of a bitch.

504
00:30:03,680 --> 00:30:05,400
- How are you doing?
- Fine.

505
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:09,080
- Who is it today?
- Billy Phelps.

506
00:30:09,120 --> 00:30:10,000
Who are you?

507
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:13,320
Fly me. I'm your friendly
Portuguese airline.

508
00:30:13,560 --> 00:30:14,760
She's Infernal Affairs.

509
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:15,800
How'd you know?

510
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:19,480
I took the liberty
of looking at your file folder.

511
00:30:19,720 --> 00:30:21,520
Lorna Cole.

512
00:30:21,760 --> 00:30:24,440
- And you're Sergeant Murtaugh.
- I used to be.

513
00:30:24,680 --> 00:30:27,480
What's Infernal Repairs
want with our collar?

514
00:30:27,720 --> 00:30:29,040
We're taking over, thanks.

515
00:30:29,280 --> 00:30:31,040
Nobody told us they were taking over.

516
00:30:31,280 --> 00:30:33,320
Nobody has to tell you anything,
Patrolman.

517
00:30:33,560 --> 00:30:35,280
I want to go and see the captain.

518
00:30:35,520 --> 00:30:38,000
You want to see the captain?
Let's go see the captain.

519
00:30:38,240 --> 00:30:40,680
- And put on a vest.
- Oh, are you wearing one?

520
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:44,400
Just take it easy, man.

521
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:57,520
Hey, guys. Phelps, William.
Actually, his name's Billy.

522
00:30:57,760 --> 00:30:58,880
You, too?

523
00:30:59,120 --> 00:31:00,960
- Popular guy today.
- Somebody with him?

524
00:31:01,200 --> 00:31:04,120
No, not really.
He's down the hall to the right.

525
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:06,720
Want to sign in here, Sarge?

526
00:31:06,960 --> 00:31:08,200
Miss.

527
00:31:08,440 --> 00:31:11,880
- What's Internal Affairs doing here?
- Don't start. I just found out myself.

528
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:14,280
This is Herman Walters,
Chief of Intelligence.

529
00:31:14,520 --> 00:31:16,440
You haven't met his daughter,
Lorna Doone.

530
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:17,760
Pleased to meet you.

531
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:20,720
The Phelps case has been transferred
to Internal Affairs.

532
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:21,640
Why?

533
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:23,680
- I can't tell you.
- That's classified.

534
00:31:23,920 --> 00:31:26,280
We busted our buns busting this guy.
We busted him.

535
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:28,920
Busted is right.
He spent the night in the hospital.

536
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:31,040
- He didn't buckle up.
- We even cited him.

537
00:31:31,280 --> 00:31:33,000
I know, I read your report.

538
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:35,520
Our cases have, unfortunately,
crossed paths here.

539
00:31:35,760 --> 00:31:37,960
That's all I can say.
We'll take over from here.

540
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:40,280
Captain, what is she talking about here?

541
00:31:40,520 --> 00:31:42,960
- That's classified.
- No, I'm talking to him.

542
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:44,240
I'm telling you...

543
00:31:44,480 --> 00:31:46,880
No, I said, "Captain".
I'm talking to the captain.

544
00:31:47,120 --> 00:31:49,880
- That's classified.
- I'm talking to him.

545
00:31:50,120 --> 00:31:52,960
That's bullshit!

546
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:56,120
Maybe these guys
can contribute something to this case?

547
00:31:56,360 --> 00:31:59,120
From their records,
they only contribute mayhem and chaos.

548
00:31:59,360 --> 00:32:01,520
No, I'm Chaos, he's Mayhem.
We're a double act.

549
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:03,800
What are we,
required reading or something?

550
00:32:04,040 --> 00:32:05,480
As a matter of fact, you are.

551
00:32:05,720 --> 00:32:08,240
It's a cross between "Police Gazette"
and "Mad" magazine.

552
00:32:08,480 --> 00:32:11,160
- What's wrong with "Mad"?
- Nothing, I used to read it...

553
00:32:11,400 --> 00:32:12,760
You've got some taste.

554
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:15,200
...when I was 12.

555
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:16,800
- Riggs, let's go.
- I'm out of here.

556
00:32:17,040 --> 00:32:18,840
We busted him, we can talk to him.

557
00:32:19,080 --> 00:32:21,120
- Captain.
- Riggs. Murtaugh.

558
00:32:21,360 --> 00:32:24,840
Get your asses back here.

559
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:28,600
You'll be needing these.

560
00:32:28,840 --> 00:32:31,000
I'm reinstating both of you.

561
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:33,560
- Don't you just love him?
- Yeah.

562
00:32:33,800 --> 00:32:36,280
God!

563
00:32:36,760 --> 00:32:38,360
You really are a beautiful man.

564
00:32:38,600 --> 00:32:39,840
Just get rid of the blues.

565
00:32:40,080 --> 00:32:44,280
- They don't go with your ponytail.
- Absolutely not.

566
00:32:44,440 --> 00:32:45,280
Yeah, right.

567
00:32:45,520 --> 00:32:46,360
Get a haircut!

568
00:32:46,600 --> 00:32:47,680
Of course, I won't.

569
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:49,800
You've exceeded your authority, Captain.

570
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:52,800
- That's not how I see it.
- That's how the chief will see it.

571
00:32:53,040 --> 00:32:54,920
- Take it up with him.
- I think I will.

572
00:32:55,160 --> 00:32:58,400
Catch up with them. We don't want this
screwed up with cowboy tactics.

573
00:32:58,640 --> 00:33:01,240
Son of a bitch.

574
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:04,560
Hi, Billy.

575
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:06,800
Jack.

576
00:33:07,040 --> 00:33:09,560
'Bye, Billy.

577
00:33:15,440 --> 00:33:18,480
See you, Billy.

578
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:25,200
Sergeant, did you get what you need?

579
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:29,240
Not really. It's a dead issue, I'm afraid.

580
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:31,360
How long has Phelps been doing this?

581
00:33:31,600 --> 00:33:34,240
- Doing what?
- This armored-car thing.

582
00:33:34,480 --> 00:33:38,800
I wouldn't know.
I'm not interested in armored cars.

583
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:52,320
I don't think she's telling us everything.

584
00:33:52,560 --> 00:33:53,680
I think you're right.

585
00:33:53,920 --> 00:33:56,280
Boy, these six days are going to be rough.

586
00:33:56,520 --> 00:33:59,760
God, be good to me, please.

587
00:34:00,520 --> 00:34:04,320
Shit, son of a bitch knew there was
a camera in the wall.

588
00:34:04,560 --> 00:34:05,240
Damn it!

589
00:34:05,480 --> 00:34:07,920
He didn't know there was one
in the interrogation room.

590
00:34:08,160 --> 00:34:09,840
There isn't.

591
00:34:10,080 --> 00:34:11,720
We installed them six months ago.

592
00:34:11,960 --> 00:34:13,400
- Every station.
- That's great.

593
00:34:13,640 --> 00:34:15,400
Six months and we don't know about it?

594
00:34:15,640 --> 00:34:17,360
This is the "police police", Captain.

595
00:34:17,600 --> 00:34:21,160
"Police police." Very good. Can you say
that three times in a row, real fast?

596
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:23,840
- Why? Am I getting to you?
- Are you trying to bait me?

597
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:25,200
I'm a master at it.

598
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:26,320
That figures.

599
00:34:26,560 --> 00:34:28,960
Baiting master. Great, man,
try all the tricks.

600
00:34:29,200 --> 00:34:30,720
Freeze that. Stop it.

601
00:34:30,960 --> 00:34:32,280
Jack Travis.

602
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:33,280
Who?

603
00:34:33,520 --> 00:34:36,520
Lieutenant Jack Edward Travis.

604
00:34:36,760 --> 00:34:37,720
He was one of us.

605
00:34:37,960 --> 00:34:40,880
Hell of a brutal cop.
He could beat a confession out of anyone.

606
00:34:41,120 --> 00:34:42,400
One hell of a dirty cop.

607
00:34:42,640 --> 00:34:46,120
I've never seen so many suspensions
and reprimands and charges of misconduct.

608
00:34:46,360 --> 00:34:48,600
He's also as tough as they come.

609
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:49,960
What happened to him?

610
00:34:50,200 --> 00:34:51,160
I don't know.

611
00:34:51,400 --> 00:34:55,040
His partner and him were on a stakeout.
He went for coffee, never came back.

612
00:34:55,280 --> 00:34:57,640
Looks like he's had
one cappuccino too many.

613
00:34:57,880 --> 00:34:59,560
We'd better brief Walters.

614
00:34:59,800 --> 00:35:01,760
Excuse me, cute stuff.

615
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:05,040
- That's harassment.
- "Cute stuff." That's you.

616
00:35:05,280 --> 00:35:08,520
- Captain.
- Boys. It's just the captain.

617
00:35:08,760 --> 00:35:12,000
Your involvement in this case ended
when Phelps hit the floor.

618
00:35:12,240 --> 00:35:15,200
Why don't you just go back
and beat your street?

619
00:35:15,440 --> 00:35:18,200
- Now's the time to buy.
- Not now.

620
00:35:18,440 --> 00:35:20,280
- Hey, Roger.
- Not now, Leo.

621
00:35:20,520 --> 00:35:22,840
- Not now!
- We got to talk, babe, okay?

622
00:35:23,080 --> 00:35:25,080
You're in trouble. You've got termites.

623
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:26,360
Termites?

624
00:35:26,600 --> 00:35:28,520
- Oh, God!
- You're infested!

625
00:35:28,760 --> 00:35:31,080
The only thing holding up your house
is the paint.

626
00:35:31,320 --> 00:35:32,200
We should go.

627
00:35:32,440 --> 00:35:34,280
Leo, could you get the place fumigated?

628
00:35:34,520 --> 00:35:36,640
We should pull every file on this guy.

629
00:35:36,880 --> 00:35:39,000
I know this guy.
Are you watching "Geraldo"?

630
00:35:39,240 --> 00:35:40,520
- What?
- I know the guy.

631
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:43,200
- How do you know him?
- I've seen the guy before.

632
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:45,440
- Where?
- I don't know. I recognize him...

633
00:35:45,680 --> 00:35:48,800
His name is Jack Travis.
Does that ring a bell?

634
00:35:49,040 --> 00:35:51,040
Hands off the clothes. Okay?

635
00:35:51,280 --> 00:35:53,600
I'm thinking. Let me think.

636
00:35:53,840 --> 00:35:55,200
It was a big party.

637
00:35:55,440 --> 00:35:58,520
Someone brought a monkey
that knocked over the salad bar.

638
00:35:58,760 --> 00:36:01,800
And this guy comes in
and introduces me to another guy...

639
00:36:02,040 --> 00:36:04,000
...who wants a favor.

640
00:36:04,240 --> 00:36:05,760
- I got it!
- What?

641
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:07,040
He's got it!

642
00:36:07,280 --> 00:36:09,160
- I remember!
- You remember!

643
00:36:09,400 --> 00:36:12,280
Don't do it. Don't let the earring fool you.

644
00:36:12,520 --> 00:36:14,560
- We're back. We're back!
- Yeah.

645
00:36:14,800 --> 00:36:18,640
Listen. Can I have a gun this time?

646
00:36:27,920 --> 00:36:32,400
Okay, this is it! These guys always
wanted me to do favors for them!

647
00:36:32,640 --> 00:36:36,160
Like, some guys wanted broads,
another guy wanted Cuban cigars.

648
00:36:36,400 --> 00:36:38,000
Your guy, hockey.

649
00:36:38,240 --> 00:36:41,520
The best seats in the house.

650
00:36:42,560 --> 00:36:45,240
- Where're the seats?
- Yeah?

651
00:36:45,480 --> 00:36:47,720
Probably by the glass.

652
00:36:47,960 --> 00:36:50,320
Does "needle in a haystack"
mean anything to you?

653
00:36:50,560 --> 00:36:51,840
Why don't we spread out?

654
00:36:52,080 --> 00:36:56,360
If we all take a different direction,
it'd be like old times.

655
00:36:56,600 --> 00:36:59,240
Don't push, lady.
I'm on police business here.

656
00:36:59,480 --> 00:37:02,680
Just take it easy.

657
00:37:28,040 --> 00:37:31,000
{y:i}Los Angeles penalty. Number 15.

658
00:37:31,240 --> 00:37:32,960
{y:i}Two minutes for high-sticking.

659
00:37:33,200 --> 00:37:36,720
{y:i}Time, 5:15.

660
00:37:53,240 --> 00:37:55,880
{y:i}Mr. Jack Travis?

661
00:37:56,120 --> 00:37:59,880
{y:i}Mr. Jack Travis, this is the LAPD.

662
00:38:00,120 --> 00:38:01,440
{y:i}We know you're in here.

663
00:38:01,680 --> 00:38:03,720
{y:i}We know where you are.
{y:i}Just stay in your seat.

664
00:38:03,960 --> 00:38:05,240
{y:i}Don't be stupid.

665
00:38:05,480 --> 00:38:07,600
{y:i}I'll be there to escort you out in a minute.

666
00:38:07,840 --> 00:38:10,840
{y:i}There's a policeman at every exit,
{y:i}so it's no use trying to run.

667
00:38:11,080 --> 00:38:12,040
Smart son of a bitch.

668
00:38:12,280 --> 00:38:13,560
{y:i}Just stay where you are.

669
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:17,360
{y:i}Thanks for your cooperation.
{y:i}Play on, boys.

670
00:38:29,720 --> 00:38:32,320
Come on, let's go!

671
00:38:41,160 --> 00:38:44,440
Get out of my fucking way!

672
00:38:54,760 --> 00:38:57,360
Excuse me.

673
00:39:08,200 --> 00:39:11,120
You can't be on the ice!

674
00:39:16,400 --> 00:39:19,440
I got him!

675
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:24,600
You have the right... You're under arrest!

676
00:39:31,560 --> 00:39:32,440
Fucking weasel!

677
00:39:32,680 --> 00:39:34,360
What the hell's going on here?

678
00:39:34,600 --> 00:39:36,120
I'm LAPD!

679
00:39:36,360 --> 00:39:40,080
I don't care. You can't be on the ice.

680
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:45,800
I got him!

681
00:39:46,040 --> 00:39:49,520
You're all right, pal. Stay calm.

682
00:39:50,640 --> 00:39:52,280
Make sure you tell my mother.

683
00:39:52,520 --> 00:39:53,600
Where'd he go?

684
00:39:53,840 --> 00:39:56,520
Down there.

685
00:40:04,720 --> 00:40:07,920
Son of a bitch!

686
00:40:09,400 --> 00:40:12,400
He thinks I don't know I'm dying.
I know it.

687
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:15,640
- You'll be okay.
- I'm dying, Roger.

688
00:40:15,880 --> 00:40:17,440
I'm choking, see?

689
00:40:17,680 --> 00:40:19,520
This is what they do when they die.

690
00:40:19,760 --> 00:40:23,120
Leo, it's going to be okay.

691
00:40:23,120 --> 00:40:25,080
My body's numb. I can't feel it.

692
00:40:25,320 --> 00:40:28,160
I'm going to die, I know it. What?

693
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:31,600
You're lying on the ice.

694
00:40:31,920 --> 00:40:34,040
- That's why I'm cold?
- That's why you're cold.

695
00:40:34,280 --> 00:40:36,480
- That's why I'm numb?
- That's why you're numb.

696
00:40:36,720 --> 00:40:38,520
But he shot me. Look at all the blood.

697
00:40:38,760 --> 00:40:42,640
- It's just a flesh wound.
- So it's okay.

698
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:51,280
He's okay. He's going to make it.
He's alive!

699
00:40:54,960 --> 00:40:59,320
- Bring him this way.
- I can't believe this.

700
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:01,400
- I can't believe I got shot.
- Calm down.

701
00:41:01,640 --> 00:41:02,680
Riggs, are you here?

702
00:41:02,920 --> 00:41:05,440
We're all the same now. We all got shot.

703
00:41:05,680 --> 00:41:07,200
You'll be fine.

704
00:41:07,440 --> 00:41:08,080
Relax.

705
00:41:08,320 --> 00:41:11,000
I'm fine. There's nothing wrong with me.
I can take this.

706
00:41:11,240 --> 00:41:14,240
Calm down. We'll take care of it.
You'll be out of here tonight.

707
00:41:14,480 --> 00:41:15,400
It's no big deal.

708
00:41:15,640 --> 00:41:18,120
That's not a good idea.
You shouldn't rush this, Doc.

709
00:41:18,360 --> 00:41:19,360
You should rest up.

710
00:41:19,600 --> 00:41:21,400
A dum-dum wound can be serious.

711
00:41:21,640 --> 00:41:23,400
What's a "dum-dum wound"?

712
00:41:23,640 --> 00:41:27,320
You don't know? A guy on the Force
got his thumb shot off by a dum-dum.

713
00:41:27,560 --> 00:41:29,600
From the shock,
he was dead two days later.

714
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:31,160
"Dead two days later"?

715
00:41:31,400 --> 00:41:32,720
He died from dum-dums?

716
00:41:32,960 --> 00:41:35,200
- We'll keep you overnight.
- Make it two.

717
00:41:35,440 --> 00:41:36,280
Two days?

718
00:41:36,520 --> 00:41:38,200
Okay, we'll keep him in two days.

719
00:41:38,440 --> 00:41:39,920
Is that Leo's chart?

720
00:41:40,160 --> 00:41:43,160
- Two days, then you'll be as good as new.
- I should be with them.

721
00:41:43,400 --> 00:41:45,560
I should be with...

722
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:47,360
How do you spell, "proctological"?

723
00:41:47,600 --> 00:41:49,280
Rectal exam?

724
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:52,160
- No, you can't do that to Leo.
- Sure, we can.

725
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:53,160
Why's she...

726
00:41:53,400 --> 00:41:55,040
Please, Mr. Getz.

727
00:41:55,280 --> 00:41:58,400
You've been shot in the arm?
Let her take it. You'll get it back.

728
00:41:58,640 --> 00:42:02,040
There's a clock in your room.

729
00:42:02,080 --> 00:42:03,920
Does this look like a "dum-dum wound"?

730
00:42:04,160 --> 00:42:06,400
- It sounded like one when it happened.
- Shit.

731
00:42:06,640 --> 00:42:10,360
- Take it easy. Two days.
- Two days and you'll be out. No problem.

732
00:42:10,600 --> 00:42:13,200
- I'll see you guys.
- We won't make a move without you.

733
00:42:13,440 --> 00:42:15,400
I thought that bullet sounded different.

734
00:42:15,640 --> 00:42:18,160
- Relax. They'll be there when you get out.
- I'm fine.

735
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:20,160
- You own your house, Doc?
- What?

736
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:22,160
- You don't recognize my face?
- No, sir.

737
00:42:22,400 --> 00:42:24,080
Watch.

738
00:42:24,320 --> 00:42:24,800
It's about time.

739
00:42:25,040 --> 00:42:27,680
These doggy treats are okay,
but I need some human food.

740
00:42:27,920 --> 00:42:31,160
Don't worry. I'll make you the best thing
you've ever had.

741
00:42:31,400 --> 00:42:33,840
Good.

742
00:42:34,080 --> 00:42:38,080
- You ever eaten one of my hamburgers?
- I've been lucky so far.

743
00:42:38,320 --> 00:42:39,360
Hey, Fast Eddie.

744
00:42:39,600 --> 00:42:41,680
- How's business?
- Booming. Can't you tell?

745
00:42:41,920 --> 00:42:44,200
Yeah, I'm looking at it.
Did you meet my partner?

746
00:42:44,440 --> 00:42:46,880
I want to cook one
