00:59:17,240 --> 00:59:21,560
We got hurt often, but if no bones were
broken or blood gushed, nobody cared.

1002
00:59:21,800 --> 00:59:23,040
Look, blood. See? Blood.

1003
00:59:23,280 --> 00:59:24,600
It's not gushing.

1004
00:59:24,840 --> 00:59:27,160
It was free flowing earlier.

1005
00:59:27,400 --> 00:59:33,400
Could you bring me a needle and thread?
Some peroxide. I'll patch it up myself.

1006
00:59:34,680 --> 00:59:36,040
Don't touch anything.

1007
00:59:36,280 --> 00:59:39,040
I wasn't.

1008
00:59:39,240 --> 00:59:42,320
What's with you?

1009
00:59:57,000 --> 00:59:58,440
What are you doing?

1010
00:59:58,680 --> 01:00:01,120
- I said not to touch anything.
- It came on by itself.

1011
01:00:01,360 --> 01:00:03,240
All by itself? What are you, a wise guy?

1012
01:00:03,480 --> 01:00:05,320
You don't like to share your toys, do you?

1013
01:00:05,560 --> 01:00:07,240
- This isn't a toy.
- What is it?

1014
01:00:07,480 --> 01:00:09,160
- This is a weapon.
- A weapon?

1015
01:00:09,400 --> 01:00:11,480
Used properly, a very effective weapon.

1016
01:00:11,720 --> 01:00:13,480
What, do you throw it at people?

1017
01:00:13,720 --> 01:00:16,280
You'll give yourself a hernia.
Come here. Sit down.

1018
01:00:16,520 --> 01:00:17,480
Right here.

1019
01:00:17,720 --> 01:00:21,840
- Take a little off the top...
- Right here.

1020
01:00:25,640 --> 01:00:27,600
Do you bring all your interrogations home?

1021
01:00:27,840 --> 01:00:30,040
- What are we talking about?
- It's back here.

1022
01:00:30,280 --> 01:00:31,840
- Careful, careful.
- Turn your head.

1023
01:00:32,080 --> 01:00:33,320
- Careful.
- This?

1024
01:00:33,560 --> 01:00:35,960
- This scratch?
- It feels like the Grand Canyon.

1025
01:00:36,200 --> 01:00:37,800
Oh, God.

1026
01:00:38,040 --> 01:00:40,160
Hold still.

1027
01:00:40,400 --> 01:00:43,400
Oh, God. We haven't even started.

1028
01:00:43,640 --> 01:00:45,320
Be gentle with me.

1029
01:00:45,560 --> 01:00:48,840
I see this isn't virgin territory.
What is this? A knife?

1030
01:00:49,080 --> 01:00:51,880
That's an ax.
Some guy mistook my head for a log.

1031
01:00:52,120 --> 01:00:54,640
- That's a natural mistake.
- What, I have a wooden head?

1032
01:00:54,880 --> 01:00:56,160
- Look at that.
- A knife.

1033
01:00:56,400 --> 01:00:58,120
Knife? That's very nice.

1034
01:00:58,360 --> 01:00:59,360
This is all right.

1035
01:00:59,600 --> 01:01:01,880
That's a pavement,
dragged down Crenshaw.

1036
01:01:02,120 --> 01:01:04,920
That's great. Look at that texture.
Look at this.

1037
01:01:05,160 --> 01:01:07,040
Same thing. Third and Highland.

1038
01:01:07,280 --> 01:01:09,840
- Dragged for about half a block.
- That's a good one.

1039
01:01:10,080 --> 01:01:12,120
Feel that texture. Cheese-grater time.

1040
01:01:12,360 --> 01:01:14,160
- Moving truck.
- Moving truck?

1041
01:01:14,400 --> 01:01:15,200
Moving bullet.

1042
01:01:15,440 --> 01:01:18,360
- Moving bullet?
- Here. This is the best.

1043
01:01:18,600 --> 01:01:21,200
- It goes all the way through to the back.
- Right through?

1044
01:01:21,440 --> 01:01:22,920
You're lucky. Was it a.22?

1045
01:01:23,160 --> 01:01:24,520
It's a.38.

1046
01:01:24,760 --> 01:01:27,400
- It's a.38.
- That? That's wimpy. This is a.38.

1047
01:01:27,640 --> 01:01:30,320
Yours is bigger than mine?
I don't think so.

1048
01:01:30,560 --> 01:01:31,720
Maybe not, but look.

1049
01:01:31,960 --> 01:01:34,720
A whole family of.44s on the back.

1050
01:01:34,960 --> 01:01:35,800
There they are.

1051
01:01:36,040 --> 01:01:37,080
That's impressive.

1052
01:01:37,320 --> 01:01:40,440
One hit my lung. I was breathing
blood bubbles. It was disgusting.

1053
01:01:40,680 --> 01:01:41,800
Blood bubbles. Okay.

1054
01:01:42,040 --> 01:01:43,800
You got one?

1055
01:01:44,040 --> 01:01:47,160
Pump-action. 12-gauge.

1056
01:01:47,800 --> 01:01:50,000
Right down here. Went through.

1057
01:01:50,240 --> 01:01:51,600
- That must have hurt.
- Right.

1058
01:01:51,840 --> 01:01:52,640
Not too close.

1059
01:01:52,880 --> 01:01:54,960
Riggs, if he were that close, I'd be dead.

1060
01:01:55,200 --> 01:01:57,440
I can beat it.

1061
01:01:57,680 --> 01:01:59,960
- I'll take your word for it.
- You gotta see this.

1062
01:02:00,200 --> 01:02:01,960
- I believe you.
- This guy had a knife.

1063
01:02:02,200 --> 01:02:06,120
You'll love it. He stuck it in my leg
and ran it around eight times.

1064
01:02:06,360 --> 01:02:08,280
- I'll take your word for it.
- Look!

1065
01:02:08,520 --> 01:02:09,760
No, I said forget it.

1066
01:02:10,000 --> 01:02:11,360
This is a blue-ribbon event.

1067
01:02:11,600 --> 01:02:13,400
Forget it.

1068
01:02:13,640 --> 01:02:14,720
You started this.

1069
01:02:14,960 --> 01:02:17,400
- Yeah, I can end it.
- You know what?

1070
01:02:17,640 --> 01:02:20,440
You're a very poor loser.

1071
01:02:20,560 --> 01:02:21,480
I didn't lose.

1072
01:02:21,720 --> 01:02:23,840
- Yes, you did.
- No, I didn't lose.

1073
01:02:24,080 --> 01:02:25,240
- You lost.
- I conceded.

1074
01:02:25,480 --> 01:02:27,720
There's a difference between losing
and conceding.

1075
01:02:27,960 --> 01:02:29,680
You conceded or you're conceited?

1076
01:02:29,920 --> 01:02:31,520
- You think I'm conceited?
- Yeah.

1077
01:02:31,760 --> 01:02:33,560
Tell me you lost. Admit to it.

1078
01:02:33,800 --> 01:02:34,960
I'll get you a Band-Aid.

1079
01:02:35,200 --> 01:02:39,240
- Tell me you lost.
- I said don't touch anything...

1080
01:02:49,400 --> 01:02:52,440
You're going to smack
the shit out of me, right?

1081
01:02:52,680 --> 01:02:55,960
I can do better than that.

1082
01:03:10,920 --> 01:03:13,840
This could be a serious ethical breach here.

1083
01:03:14,080 --> 01:03:16,280
I never made it
with another sergeant before.

1084
01:03:16,520 --> 01:03:19,160
Shut up, Riggs.

1085
01:03:52,560 --> 01:03:56,360
{y:i}I'm as hungry as a whale.
{y:i}Bring on the food.

1086
01:03:56,880 --> 01:03:58,600
He's got a sense of humor.

1087
01:03:58,840 --> 01:04:02,160
Watch this. This is a good bit.

1088
01:04:06,040 --> 01:04:09,560
I think you're gonna get on just fine.

1089
01:04:14,280 --> 01:04:17,680
If you could pry yourself away
from doggie heaven, I'm finished out here.

1090
01:04:17,920 --> 01:04:22,360
- You wanna take a look?
- Sure. Let's go outside for some air.

1091
01:04:24,440 --> 01:04:25,720
One for you.

1092
01:04:25,960 --> 01:04:27,240
One for you. No favorites.

1093
01:04:27,480 --> 01:04:29,600
I just have to finish the flashing here...

1094
01:04:29,840 --> 01:04:32,240
...and the roofing shingles
about another few bundles.

1095
01:04:32,480 --> 01:04:34,560
Unless it rains, it should hold up all right.

1096
01:04:34,800 --> 01:04:37,400
That's comforting.

1097
01:04:40,120 --> 01:04:42,840
I like a man who takes pride in his work.

1098
01:04:43,080 --> 01:04:44,720
Do you know where I can find one?

1099
01:04:44,960 --> 01:04:47,000
Like trying to find a cop
when you need one.

1100
01:04:47,240 --> 01:04:48,600
We're not mind readers.

1101
01:04:48,840 --> 01:04:50,520
You have to have a mind to read.

1102
01:04:50,760 --> 01:04:51,720
Read it and weep.

1103
01:04:51,960 --> 01:04:54,360
With these prices
you're promoting graft in the port.

1104
01:04:54,600 --> 01:04:58,640
If there's anybody
who knows about graft, it's you.

1105
01:04:58,680 --> 01:05:01,600
- Hi, Martin.
- How are you doing?

1106
01:05:01,840 --> 01:05:03,120
- Hi, Mickey.
- Hi, Rianne.

1107
01:05:03,360 --> 01:05:05,520
What are you doing here?

1108
01:05:05,760 --> 01:05:07,040
Or shouldn't I ask?

1109
01:05:07,280 --> 01:05:09,120
You got a sink to unplug?

1110
01:05:09,360 --> 01:05:10,920
- I got your sink.
- Good. Go do it.

1111
01:05:11,160 --> 01:05:13,960
I'll see you next week.

1112
01:05:18,320 --> 01:05:20,000
What's up?

1113
01:05:20,240 --> 01:05:21,960
Dad didn't come home last night.

1114
01:05:22,200 --> 01:05:25,160
He always comes home.

1115
01:05:54,280 --> 01:05:57,560
Oh, damn, Riggs.

1116
01:05:58,440 --> 01:05:59,480
What do you want?

1117
01:05:59,720 --> 01:06:01,720
I just wanted to see how you were doing.

1118
01:06:01,960 --> 01:06:03,760
Who sent you? Trish?

1119
01:06:04,000 --> 01:06:06,160
You're doing pretty well.
Trish didn't send me.

1120
01:06:06,400 --> 01:06:08,720
Rianne came to see me.
She asked me to find you.

1121
01:06:08,960 --> 01:06:09,840
To your place?

1122
01:06:10,080 --> 01:06:11,240
Well, that's where I am.

1123
01:06:11,480 --> 01:06:15,160
- My daughter came to your trailer?
- Yeah.

1124
01:06:15,400 --> 01:06:19,480
- My daughter came to your trailer?
- Come on, she was worried.

1125
01:06:19,720 --> 01:06:21,360
Get off of my boat, Riggs!

1126
01:06:21,600 --> 01:06:23,280
- Come on.
- Get off my boat!

1127
01:06:23,520 --> 01:06:24,840
You're drunk.

1128
01:06:25,080 --> 01:06:27,080
That's something you should know about.

1129
01:06:27,320 --> 01:06:29,800
- This isn't going to do you any good.
- Give me that.

1130
01:06:30,040 --> 01:06:30,920
Give me that.

1131
01:06:31,160 --> 01:06:32,840
Roger, please don't do this.

1132
01:06:33,080 --> 01:06:36,040
You got three days until you retire.
This won't do you any good.

1133
01:06:36,280 --> 01:06:38,760
You self-righteous bastard! Give it...

1134
01:06:39,000 --> 01:06:40,640
Don't do this, okay? Please?

1135
01:06:40,880 --> 01:06:43,080
Give it to me, damn it.

1136
01:06:43,320 --> 01:06:46,680
What are you going to do now, shoot me?

1137
01:06:46,920 --> 01:06:47,680
There.

1138
01:06:47,920 --> 01:06:50,360
Take your finger out of my bottle.
Give me that gun.

1139
01:06:50,600 --> 01:06:52,760
The bottle's going sailing.

1140
01:06:53,000 --> 01:06:55,960
Son of a bitch!

1141
01:06:58,720 --> 01:07:00,040
Not bad for an old man.

1142
01:07:00,280 --> 01:07:01,320
Are you finished?

1143
01:07:01,560 --> 01:07:04,120
No, I got another bottle in the galley
and I'll get it.

1144
01:07:04,360 --> 01:07:05,320
No, you're not.

1145
01:07:05,560 --> 01:07:07,440
Don't do this to yourself.

1146
01:07:07,680 --> 01:07:10,280
You gotta cut this out.

1147
01:07:10,520 --> 01:07:12,840
Oh, man, I'm sorry. Are you okay?

1148
01:07:13,080 --> 01:07:16,120
Come on. Sit down.

1149
01:07:16,560 --> 01:07:18,040
- You hit me.
- Cool it, will you?

1150
01:07:18,280 --> 01:07:19,960
Cut it out. Give it up, okay?

1151
01:07:20,200 --> 01:07:21,160
Go ahead.

1152
01:07:21,400 --> 01:07:23,080
Go ahead. Hit me again.

1153
01:07:23,320 --> 01:07:25,680
I don't want to hit you.
You think I like this shit?

1154
01:07:25,920 --> 01:07:28,360
Hit me again. You think I'm afraid of you...

1155
01:07:28,600 --> 01:07:30,920
- I know you're not.
...and that kung-fu shit?

1156
01:07:31,160 --> 01:07:33,240
Please, Rog.

1157
01:07:33,480 --> 01:07:36,680
That kid was a killer, all right.
That wasn't a toy in his hand.

1158
01:07:36,920 --> 01:07:40,240
That was a machine pistol
with twin carbines and all the trimmings.

1159
01:07:40,480 --> 01:07:43,800
He would have drilled you, me,
anybody that came along.

1160
01:07:44,040 --> 01:07:45,480
You had no choice.

1161
01:07:45,720 --> 01:07:47,800
It didn't happen to you. It happened to me.

1162
01:07:48,040 --> 01:07:49,320
It happened to me!

1163
01:07:49,560 --> 01:07:51,560
My God, I killed that kid!

1164
01:07:51,800 --> 01:07:53,000
I killed that boy.

1165
01:07:53,240 --> 01:07:55,000
You've killed a lot of people.

1166
01:07:55,240 --> 01:07:58,440
You've killed a fucking lot of people!
You don't kill a baby.

1167
01:07:58,680 --> 01:08:01,680
You've got ice in your veins.
You don't kill a boy like Nick.

1168
01:08:01,920 --> 01:08:03,320
You selfish bastard!

1169
01:08:03,560 --> 01:08:05,160
You selfish bastard!

1170
01:08:05,400 --> 01:08:07,560
You're just thinking about yourself.

1171
01:08:07,800 --> 01:08:09,480
What about me?

1172
01:08:09,720 --> 01:08:12,520
We're partners. We are partners.

1173
01:08:12,760 --> 01:08:14,360
What happens to you, happens to me.

1174
01:08:14,600 --> 01:08:17,640
After all the shit we've been through,
don't you get it?

1175
01:08:17,880 --> 01:08:19,880
Don't you get it?

1176
01:08:20,120 --> 01:08:23,280
When you retire, you're not just
retiring you, you're retiring us.

1177
01:08:23,520 --> 01:08:25,560
- You're retiring us.
- That's not my problem.

1178
01:08:25,800 --> 01:08:26,520
Yes, it is.

1179
01:08:26,760 --> 01:08:29,280
- It's not my problem.
- You're the only family I've got.

1180
01:08:29,520 --> 01:08:32,320
I've got three beautiful kids.
I love them and they're yours.

1181
01:08:32,560 --> 01:08:35,560
Trish does my laundry.
I live in your icebox. I live in your life!

1182
01:08:35,800 --> 01:08:37,160
What am I going to do?

1183
01:08:37,400 --> 01:08:38,760
- I don't care.
- Yes, you do.

1184
01:08:39,000 --> 01:08:40,280
- I don't care.
- Yes, you do.

1185
01:08:40,520 --> 01:08:41,520
I don't care!

1186
01:08:41,760 --> 01:08:42,680
Yes, you do!

1187
01:08:42,920 --> 01:08:44,680
- I don't care.
- You do so.

1188
01:08:44,920 --> 01:08:47,800
I don't care!

1189
01:08:51,240 --> 01:08:55,480
I don't know what I'm saying anymore.
I don't know what I'm thinking.

1190
01:08:55,720 --> 01:08:59,320
I had three days, and now this.

1191
01:08:59,480 --> 01:09:00,520
I'm sorry.

1192
01:09:00,760 --> 01:09:04,560
- That's all right.
- No, I'm really sorry.

1193
01:09:04,800 --> 01:09:08,120
I didn't realize that my retirement
was gonna screw you up.

1194
01:09:08,360 --> 01:09:12,720
Forget it. I haven't got any problems.
I was out of line saying that shit.

1195
01:09:12,960 --> 01:09:15,080
Look, man...

1196
01:09:15,320 --> 01:09:18,040
Riggs, look...

1197
01:09:18,080 --> 01:09:20,040
You know I love you.

1198
01:09:20,280 --> 01:09:25,320
You know I love you, Riggs.
And your problems are my problems.

1199
01:09:25,560 --> 01:09:28,200
Like you said, "What happens to you...

1200
01:09:28,440 --> 01:09:30,520
...happens to me." So try me.

1201
01:09:30,760 --> 01:09:32,480
I'm here for you.

1202
01:09:32,720 --> 01:09:35,200
I haven't got any problems.

1203
01:09:35,440 --> 01:09:39,280
Yes, you do. We all have problems.
You help me...

1204
01:09:39,520 --> 01:09:42,600
...and I'm gonna help you.

1205
01:09:43,960 --> 01:09:47,400
I do have a little problem.

1206
01:09:47,400 --> 01:09:49,880
You don't want to hear it.
This is piddly shit.

1207
01:09:50,120 --> 01:09:51,760
Yes, I do. I want to hear it.

1208
01:09:52,000 --> 01:09:53,840
- Tell me.
- This is ridiculous.

1209
01:09:54,080 --> 01:09:56,840
- You don't want to hear it.
- No. I'm here.

1210
01:09:57,080 --> 01:09:58,840
Well...

1211
01:09:59,080 --> 01:10:04,360
I think maybe I slept with someone
that I probably shouldn't have.

1212
01:10:04,760 --> 01:10:07,640
You son of a bitch!

1213
01:10:13,080 --> 01:10:14,000
Help me.

1214
01:10:14,240 --> 01:10:16,360
I ought to let you drown, you traitor.

1215
01:10:16,600 --> 01:10:17,600
Help me.

1216
01:10:17,840 --> 01:10:20,800
Come on in.

1217
01:10:23,280 --> 01:10:24,480
What did you hit me for?

1218
01:10:24,720 --> 01:10:27,760
'Cause you slept with Rianne.

1219
01:10:28,000 --> 01:10:28,800
I did not.

1220
01:10:29,040 --> 01:10:32,280
- Who did you sleep with?
- I slept with Sergeant Cole.

1221
01:10:32,520 --> 01:10:33,960
Sergeant Cole from Traffic?

1222
01:10:34,200 --> 01:10:36,080
No, not Sergeant Cole from Traffic.

1223
01:10:36,320 --> 01:10:39,120
Lorna. Sergeant Cole from Traffic
is her uncle.

1224
01:10:39,360 --> 01:10:43,320
- Okay. That's okay.
- Oh, I don't know.

1225
01:10:44,520 --> 01:10:45,640
Sheriff's Department.

1226
01:10:45,880 --> 01:10:46,680
Sheriff...

1227
01:10:46,920 --> 01:10:49,240
We're LAPD.

1228
01:10:49,480 --> 01:10:51,880
What are you boys doing down there?

1229
01:10:52,120 --> 01:10:54,440
- We're in the middle of a case.
- Yeah.

1230
01:10:54,680 --> 01:10:57,240
Of Scotch.

1231
01:10:57,920 --> 01:11:01,000
Let's get out of here.

1232
01:11:14,040 --> 01:11:17,240
Go with the grain.

1233
01:11:19,040 --> 01:11:22,120
I'll show you. Here.

1234
01:11:23,000 --> 01:11:26,360
You're going against the grain.

1235
01:11:29,400 --> 01:11:32,200
- Like that.
- Okay.

1236
01:11:37,560 --> 01:11:40,120
Are you okay?

1237
01:11:41,800 --> 01:11:45,240
Darryl was my friend, Dad.

1238
01:11:45,400 --> 01:11:48,480
I know. I'm sorry, son.

1239
01:11:48,720 --> 01:11:51,720
I hope you don't blame me.

1240
01:11:51,960 --> 01:11:54,280
I don't blame you, Dad.

1241
01:11:54,520 --> 01:11:57,400
I blame Darryl.

1242
01:12:00,040 --> 01:12:03,000
What's this right here?

1243
01:12:07,560 --> 01:12:10,520
I love you, Dad.

1244
01:12:11,960 --> 01:12:15,160
I love you, son.

1245
01:12:33,400 --> 01:12:36,760
"May he find the peace in Heaven
that eluded him on Earth."

1246
01:12:37,000 --> 01:12:38,600
"And may the scourge of violence...

1247
01:12:38,840 --> 01:12:42,160
...claiming the lives of our children
be lifted by Your grace...

1248
