1495
01:25:39,800 --> 01:25:41,160
Let's go.

1496
01:25:41,400 --> 01:25:43,880
- I'm not cut out for Internal Affairs.
- That's a switch.

1497
01:25:44,120 --> 01:25:45,840
- Right here in the building.
- Where?

1498
01:25:46,080 --> 01:25:47,920
- I'm showing you.
- Something's going down.

1499
01:25:48,160 --> 01:25:50,160
- Nothing's going down.
- I'm going with you.

1500
01:25:50,400 --> 01:25:52,560
- How old are you?
- Twenty-two today.

1501
01:25:52,800 --> 01:25:53,640
Come on.

1502
01:25:53,880 --> 01:25:55,240
Have you got protection?

1503
01:25:55,480 --> 01:25:58,000
- Right here in my wallet.
- No, your vest, you dummy.

1504
01:25:58,240 --> 01:25:59,520
Should we take him?

1505
01:25:59,760 --> 01:26:02,520
- Okay, but keep your head down.
- Stay behind me.

1506
01:26:02,760 --> 01:26:06,000
Come on, let's go. Quiet!

1507
01:26:16,680 --> 01:26:18,480
You were my ticket in.

1508
01:26:18,720 --> 01:26:22,560
It's too bad you won't be coming with me.

1509
01:26:26,280 --> 01:26:28,760
They got it all.

1510
01:26:29,000 --> 01:26:31,200
- He's dead.
- How'd they get it out of here?

1511
01:26:31,440 --> 01:26:33,440
- I don't know.
- Not upstairs.

1512
01:26:33,680 --> 01:26:36,480
Elevator.

1513
01:26:37,920 --> 01:26:39,200
Shit. It's down.

1514
01:26:39,440 --> 01:26:40,600
The subway's down there.

1515
01:26:40,840 --> 01:26:42,760
- Let's take the stairs.
- LA has subways?

1516
01:26:43,000 --> 01:26:46,320
- Where've you been?
- Read something besides the comics.

1517
01:26:46,560 --> 01:26:50,080
All right. Come on, let's hustle!

1518
01:26:51,160 --> 01:26:54,040
Hurry up, guys.

1519
01:27:05,160 --> 01:27:06,440
LAPD! Come here!

1520
01:27:06,680 --> 01:27:08,920
Come here! Step on it!

1521
01:27:09,160 --> 01:27:10,360
Son of a bitch!

1522
01:27:10,600 --> 01:27:12,600
Did you see anybody or anything strange?

1523
01:27:12,840 --> 01:27:17,320
- Lots of cops and a bunch of boxes.
- Split now. Just get out of here.

1524
01:27:17,560 --> 01:27:20,680
- I'm going across.
- I got it.

1525
01:27:25,760 --> 01:27:29,120
Get rid of Murphy, now!

1526
01:27:33,080 --> 01:27:37,280
Where the fuck do you think you're going?
Let's go.

1527
01:27:47,040 --> 01:27:50,000
Let's get out of here.

1528
01:27:50,080 --> 01:27:52,600
Cover me.

1529
01:28:10,840 --> 01:28:13,400
Let's go.

1530
01:28:21,880 --> 01:28:24,760
Stay still.

1531
01:28:32,920 --> 01:28:35,880
Happy birthday, kid.

1532
01:28:59,600 --> 01:29:02,400
Another baby.

1533
01:29:13,280 --> 01:29:14,800
Is he dead? Check the body.

1534
01:29:15,040 --> 01:29:17,840
Get me out of here!

1535
01:29:20,800 --> 01:29:23,600
Stupid son of a bitch!

1536
01:29:33,800 --> 01:29:34,640
Stop that.

1537
01:29:34,880 --> 01:29:35,720
Cut it out.

1538
01:29:35,960 --> 01:29:37,520
- Don't shoot.
- LAPD!

1539
01:29:37,760 --> 01:29:38,880
Where does this lead?

1540
01:29:39,120 --> 01:29:40,440
- Pico Station.
- Thanks.

1541
01:29:40,680 --> 01:29:41,640
Not that way.

1542
01:29:41,880 --> 01:29:45,400
Take the stairs, it's faster.

1543
01:29:57,120 --> 01:29:59,680
Gangway!

1544
01:30:05,760 --> 01:30:08,960
Get out of the way!

1545
01:30:10,360 --> 01:30:11,720
Holy shit!

1546
01:30:11,960 --> 01:30:13,480
Son of a bitch!

1547
01:30:13,720 --> 01:30:16,320
Police!

1548
01:30:21,560 --> 01:30:24,800
Step on it. There he is.

1549
01:30:25,120 --> 01:30:27,680
Goddamn!

1550
01:30:31,160 --> 01:30:34,560
Put your foot down!

1551
01:30:58,840 --> 01:31:00,040
Police!

1552
01:31:00,280 --> 01:31:01,240
I need your bike.

1553
01:31:01,480 --> 01:31:02,880
This is bullshit.

1554
01:31:03,120 --> 01:31:07,800
Sergeant Riggs, call it in.
I need a couple of clips, too.

1555
01:31:21,240 --> 01:31:24,280
Okay, we lost him.

1556
01:31:29,760 --> 01:31:32,040
Where's Riggs?

1557
01:31:32,280 --> 01:31:36,320
Keep me in touch
with the motorcycle pursuit.

1558
01:31:41,440 --> 01:31:43,040
- Shit!
- Take a right, now.

1559
01:31:43,280 --> 01:31:44,040
Take a right.

1560
01:31:44,280 --> 01:31:46,560
Go!

1561
01:31:48,280 --> 01:31:51,080
Take a right! No, left!

1562
01:32:29,520 --> 01:32:33,160
This is 6-William-6.
I'm at the freeway construction site.

1563
01:32:33,400 --> 01:32:35,280
Where's Riggs? I'm here. Where's Riggs?

1564
01:32:35,520 --> 01:32:37,800
Come back to me, Central.

1565
01:32:38,040 --> 01:32:41,000
Where the hell is Riggs?

1566
01:32:41,000 --> 01:32:42,440
Take a left here! Get off!

1567
01:32:42,680 --> 01:32:45,560
Get off the freeway!

1568
01:32:55,360 --> 01:32:58,040
Stop! Hold it!

1569
01:32:58,080 --> 01:32:59,720
Shit!

1570
01:32:59,960 --> 01:33:02,360
Hang on!

1571
01:33:15,720 --> 01:33:18,760
Where is the pursuit?

1572
01:33:21,080 --> 01:33:23,480
Shit!

1573
01:33:36,120 --> 01:33:37,400
Relax, Riggs.

1574
01:33:37,640 --> 01:33:40,240
Relax?

1575
01:33:42,960 --> 01:33:45,520
Shit!

1576
01:33:58,160 --> 01:34:00,560
Just get back. Get back!

1577
01:34:00,800 --> 01:34:03,120
Riggs, talk to me.

1578
01:34:03,360 --> 01:34:05,800
Riggs, you're alive.

1579
01:34:06,040 --> 01:34:07,440
Don't move.

1580
01:34:07,680 --> 01:34:09,520
Just get back.

1581
01:34:09,760 --> 01:34:12,480
Are you all right?

1582
01:34:17,560 --> 01:34:18,960
Don't touch me!

1583
01:34:19,200 --> 01:34:22,440
Okay! I'm not touching you!

1584
01:34:22,680 --> 01:34:25,880
Don't touch me!

1585
01:34:29,240 --> 01:34:33,080
- Don't touch me.
- I won't touch you.

1586
01:34:36,000 --> 01:34:38,920
- Are you okay now?
- I'm pissed. Now I'm pissed.

1587
01:34:39,160 --> 01:34:40,360
- Now what?
- That bastard!

1588
01:34:40,600 --> 01:34:42,600
He's done this twice now. Damn!

1589
01:34:42,840 --> 01:34:45,600
Son of a gun,
I'll suck his eyes down through his nose.

1590
01:34:45,840 --> 01:34:49,000
That's twice he's got away.
Nobody gets away from me.

1591
01:34:49,240 --> 01:34:50,800
Just relax.

1592
01:34:51,040 --> 01:34:52,720
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm okay.

1593
01:34:52,960 --> 01:34:56,320
- Are you okay?
- I'm okay.

1594
01:34:59,800 --> 01:35:01,200
- I'm having that.
- You quit!

1595
01:35:01,440 --> 01:35:05,640
I ran out of biscuits, okay?
Give me a break.

1596
01:35:07,680 --> 01:35:10,200
Oh, shit!

1597
01:35:13,080 --> 01:35:15,480
Perfect.

1598
01:35:15,480 --> 01:35:17,320
What'd I miss?

1599
01:35:17,560 --> 01:35:19,640
- What are you doing here?
- Great car chase.

1600
01:35:19,880 --> 01:35:21,760
- Great chase.
- What are you doing here?

1601
01:35:22,000 --> 01:35:23,720
- How'd you find us?
- Police scanner.

1602
01:35:23,960 --> 01:35:26,760
What are you doing with a police scanner?

1603
01:35:27,000 --> 01:35:30,320
Hello, Car 54, where are you?
I cracked this case for you guys.

1604
01:35:30,560 --> 01:35:32,200
Listen. Mesa Verde's legit.

1605
01:35:32,440 --> 01:35:34,680
They got a housing project,
called Rancho Arroyo.

1606
01:35:34,920 --> 01:35:37,200
- I know where that is.
- Why don't we check it out?

1607
01:35:37,440 --> 01:35:39,000
- That's a good idea.
- Yeah, okay.

1608
01:35:39,240 --> 01:35:40,320
I'll come with you.

1609
01:35:40,560 --> 01:35:42,320
- You're not coming with us.
- Yes, I am.

1610
01:35:42,560 --> 01:35:43,560
I'll take my car.

1611
01:35:43,800 --> 01:35:46,440
- No, you're not.
- Yes, I am.

1612
01:35:46,680 --> 01:35:50,720
I can't believe you did that! I got a spare!

1613
01:35:52,240 --> 01:35:53,880
- You're driving.
- No, I'm driving.

1614
01:35:54,120 --> 01:35:58,240
How could you do that?
I can't believe you did that.

1615
01:35:58,480 --> 01:35:59,600
Where's Lorna?

1616
01:35:59,840 --> 01:36:03,200
I can't believe you did that!

1617
01:36:03,960 --> 01:36:05,000
I can't believe it.

1618
01:36:05,240 --> 01:36:08,040
How could you do that to me?

1619
01:36:08,280 --> 01:36:09,320
Did you see that?

1620
01:36:09,560 --> 01:36:12,840
They're my partners.
I can't believe they did that!

1621
01:36:13,080 --> 01:36:16,040
Do you own your own home?

1622
01:36:46,880 --> 01:36:49,360
- Looks like we came to the right place.
- Yeah.

1623
01:36:49,600 --> 01:36:51,440
Move on out to Travis Town.

1624
01:36:51,680 --> 01:36:53,960
Great place to raise a family.

1625
01:36:54,200 --> 01:36:56,200
Built on guns and bloodshed.

1626
01:36:56,440 --> 01:36:58,720
One hell of a retirement plan
this asshole's got.

1627
01:36:58,960 --> 01:37:01,800
Let's foreclose on this son of a bitch.

1628
01:37:02,040 --> 01:37:04,120
- Say, is that...
- Darryl's gun.

1629
01:37:04,360 --> 01:37:06,880
- I've been saving it for the right occasion.
- This is it.

1630
01:37:07,120 --> 01:37:09,320
- How many men do you think he has?
- Who knows?

1631
01:37:09,560 --> 01:37:11,440
Maybe I should run over there
and ask him?

1632
01:37:11,680 --> 01:37:12,840
That'd be too easy.

1633
01:37:13,080 --> 01:37:15,440
Wish I had some grenades
or a rocket launcher.

1634
01:37:15,680 --> 01:37:17,840
Maybe a ground-to-air missile.

1635
01:37:18,080 --> 01:37:21,920
I wonder what Murphy's got in his trunk.

1636
01:37:22,400 --> 01:37:25,000
It's obvious Murphy
was never a Boy Scout.

1637
01:37:25,240 --> 01:37:28,640
Not even a good spare.

1638
01:37:30,520 --> 01:37:31,880
Put your hands down...

1639
01:37:32,120 --> 01:37:35,080
...it's embarrassing.

1640
01:37:35,480 --> 01:37:36,560
How are you doing?

1641
01:37:36,800 --> 01:37:37,600
Kissing.

1642
01:37:37,840 --> 01:37:39,040
Fresh ones?

1643
01:37:39,280 --> 01:37:40,880
Oh, yeah. Shaving cuts.

1644
01:37:41,120 --> 01:37:42,440
No points for those.

1645
01:37:42,680 --> 01:37:45,240
- How'd you get here?
- Drove.

1646
01:37:45,480 --> 01:37:48,600
I ran into Leo at the police station.
He talked to me first.

1647
01:37:48,840 --> 01:37:50,920
- Any ideas?
- Lucky thing we've got a plan.

1648
01:37:51,160 --> 01:37:52,520
Lucky thing. What is it?

1649
01:37:52,760 --> 01:37:54,960
I want it to be a surprise.

1650
01:37:55,200 --> 01:37:58,200
I like surprises.

1651
01:38:02,040 --> 01:38:04,760
Move it!

1652
01:38:05,560 --> 01:38:08,800
- Check it out.
- Let's go.

1653
01:38:24,360 --> 01:38:27,160
- Look what they did to Murph's car.
- It could've been worse.

1654
01:38:27,400 --> 01:38:30,600
- It could've been yours.
- Worse, it could've been Trish's car.

1655
01:38:30,840 --> 01:38:32,000
- On three.
- Three.

1656
01:38:32,240 --> 01:38:34,280
Three?

1657
01:38:34,520 --> 01:38:36,480
One...

1658
01:38:36,720 --> 01:38:37,680
...two...
- Three!

1659
01:38:37,920 --> 01:38:40,440
Police! Freeze!

1660
01:38:40,800 --> 01:38:43,320
Oh, shit!

1661
01:38:51,800 --> 01:38:55,000
- Let's go!
- Right now!

1662
01:39:00,920 --> 01:39:03,560
What's wrong with you?
I said go on three, not two.

1663
01:39:03,800 --> 01:39:04,920
On three.

1664
01:39:05,160 --> 01:39:06,280
It's always three.

1665
01:39:06,520 --> 01:39:08,080
Boys!

1666
01:39:08,320 --> 01:39:12,600
What are we doing here?
Losing our heads in a crisis?

1667
01:39:14,200 --> 01:39:17,080
Cover me!

1668
01:39:34,360 --> 01:39:36,960
Exxon.

1669
01:39:39,960 --> 01:39:41,480
- What?
- Count to 20.

1670
01:39:41,720 --> 01:39:42,240
What?

1671
01:39:42,480 --> 01:39:46,040
Count to 20 and then light me.

1672
01:39:48,960 --> 01:39:51,320
Shit!

1673
01:39:52,480 --> 01:39:55,800
Riggs, it's loaded with ammo!

1674
01:40:07,600 --> 01:40:10,640
- Cover me.
- Cover you?

1675
01:40:11,000 --> 01:40:12,240
Cover you, cover Riggs.

1676
01:40:12,480 --> 01:40:16,280
When's someone gonna cover me
for a change?

1677
01:40:19,640 --> 01:40:23,600
What's that, 13, 14? To hell with it.

1678
01:40:37,800 --> 01:40:41,680
It's the cops. They're burning everything.

1679
01:40:51,320 --> 01:40:52,160
Son of a bitch!

1680
01:40:52,400 --> 01:40:55,440
Crazy motherfucker!

1681
01:40:58,160 --> 01:40:58,880
Damn!

1682
01:40:59,120 --> 01:41:02,680
Riggs, the ammo! Get out of there!

1683
01:41:16,800 --> 01:41:18,880
You crazy son of a bitch!

1684
01:41:19,120 --> 01:41:21,560
Yeah!

1685
01:41:35,480 --> 01:41:39,160
Son of a bitch. You're full of shit.

1686
01:41:41,640 --> 01:41:42,920
Stay there.

1687
01:41:43,160 --> 01:41:46,040
Shit, where's Riggs?

1688
01:41:58,160 --> 01:42:01,240
Son of a bitch! No clip.

1689
01:42:02,040 --> 01:42:04,920
Lorna, no, don't!

1690
01:42:10,080 --> 01:42:11,760
Come on in, bitch.

1691
01:42:12,000 --> 01:42:14,560
The door's open!

1692
01:42:36,240 --> 01:42:39,640
I'm gonna eat your fucking heart!

1693
01:43:04,400 --> 01:43:07,360
Son of a bitch.

1694
01:43:10,960 --> 01:43:13,280
Shit!

1695
01:43:25,400 --> 01:43:27,200
Armor-piercing bullets, yeah.

1696
01:43:27,440 --> 01:43:29,720
Cop killers.

1697
01:43:29,960 --> 01:43:33,080
You're coming with me!

1698
01:43:39,760 --> 01:43:42,560
Fuck you, asshole!

1699
01:43:58,960 --> 01:44:01,000
Get up!

1700
01:44:01,240 --> 01:44:02,400
Get up!

1701
01:44:02,640 --> 01:44:06,600
Killed in the line of duty.

1702
01:44:08,440 --> 01:44:12,880
You'll get a great funeral
from the Department.

1703
01:44:17,200 --> 01:44:20,240
Cop killers.

1704
01:44:30,120 --> 01:44:33,160
Ex-cop killers.

1705
01:44:41,720 --> 01:44:44,400
Go to hell, Riggs.

1706
01:44:44,640 --> 01:44:47,280
You first.

1707
01:44:56,080 --> 01:44:58,880
Crazy son of a bitch!

1708
01:45:03,120 --> 01:45:06,960
Sorry, honey, I gotta do it. I gotta look.

1709
01:45:07,760 --> 01:45:09,440
Just hold still.

1710
01:45:09,680 --> 01:45:11,800
Get a chopper, man.

1711
01:45:12,040 --> 01:45:14,120
She had two vests on.
She's gonna be okay.

1712
01:45:14,360 --> 01:45:16,480
A couple of bad ones.
We need to get a chopper.

1713
01:45:16,720 --> 01:45:20,520
You're all right, partner. Hang on.

1714
01:45:20,760 --> 01:45:23,560
It's okay. Just lie still.

1715
01:45:23,800 --> 01:45:26,880
Just a romantic evening by the fire,
just the two of us.

1716
01:45:27,120 --> 01:45:29,720
Just be still.

1717
01:45:37,880 --> 01:45:40,680
Honey, open your eyes.

1718
01:45:40,920 --> 01:45:43,640
Open your eyes.

1719
01:45:45,880 --> 01:45:47,880
What are you trying to prove out there?

1720
01:45:48,120 --> 01:45:49,800
Why do you do that?

1721
01:45:50,040 --> 01:45:53,240
- Can I take this off?
- Yeah.

1722
01:45:53,720 --> 01:45:59,000
You're supposed to grow old
with someone, not because of them.

1723
01:46:03,160 --> 01:46:05,000
I'm gonna be with you.

1724
01:46:05,240 --> 01:46:07,280
I'm with you now. Look, I'm right here.

1725
01:46:07,520 --> 01:46:10,960
We're both here, right? Right.

1726
01:46:11,120 --> 01:46:12,880
Come on, I want to be with you.

1727
01:46:13,120 --> 01:46:15,680
What have you got to lose?

1728
01:46:15,920 --> 01:46:18,320
You.

1729
01:46:18,840 --> 01:46:21,560
Not likely.

1730
01:46:25,240 --> 01:46:28,200
- Hey, Lorna.
- Yeah?

1731
01:46:29,680 --> 01:46:33,040
Let's live to regret this.

1732
01:46:36,080 --> 01:46:37,640
- We've got to go, sir.
- Okay.

1733
01:46:37,880 --> 01:46:40,760
She's gonna be fine.

1734
01:46:43,120 --> 01:46:45,640
Can you hear me?

1735
01:46:45,880 --> 01:46:48,440
I love you.

1736
01:47:03,680 --> 01:47:08,160
"Happy retirement, Daddy"

1737
01:47:08,400 --> 01:47:12,360
"Happy retirement, Daddy"

1738
01:47:12,600 --> 01:47:15,240
This is it. This is the day.

1739
01:47:15,480 --> 01:47:16,440
Everybody? Daddy?

1740
01:47:16,680 --> 01:47:19,520
I want you to know there's a candle
for every year in the Force.

1741
01:47:19,760 --> 01:47:21,760
Yes! A lot of years.

1742
01:47:22,000 --> 01:47:25,680
- You have to blow it out.
- Come on.

1743
01:47:26,520 --> 01:47:27,240
I can't.

1744
01:47:27,480 --> 01:47:30,120
- Come on, blow it out.
- That's not what I mean.

1745
01:47:30,360 --> 01:47:31,760
What?

1746
01:47:32,000 --> 01:47:34,720
I can't retire.

1747
01:47:34,960 --> 01:47:38,120
I thought I could. I wanted to.

1748
01:47:38,360 --> 01:47:40,920
But I can't.

1749
01:47:43,720 --> 01:47:45,920
That means you're gonna
stay with the Force?

1750
01:47:46,160 --> 01:47:50,000
That means I'm staying
with the Force, baby.

1751
01:47:50,960 --> 01:47:55,560
This cake's about to explode,
so you'd better blow out these candles.

1752
01:47:55,800 --> 01:47:59,040
I want you to know
that I'm behind you all the way.

1753
01:47:59,280 --> 01:48:00,880
- Me, too.
- So am I, Dad.

1754
01:48:01,120 --> 01:48:02,000
It's okay.

1755
01:48:02,240 --> 01:48:07,040
Well, the streets will be safer
for another couple of years.

1756
01:48:07,320 --> 01:48:08,640
"Word", Nick?

1757
01:48:08,880 --> 01:48:11,480
"Word", Dad.

1758
01:48:12,880 --> 01:48:15,080
Blow them out!

1759
01:48:15,320 --> 01:48:16,360
Hello?

1760
01:48:16,600 --> 01:48:18,720
Hello! In here!

1761
01:48:18,960 --> 01:48:22,200
Hello. I gotta talk to Roger.

1762
01:48:22,360 --> 01:48:23,560
Oprah should see this.

1763
01:48:23,800 --> 01:48:25,920
I can't believe this. Okay, this is great.

1764
01:48:26,160 --> 01:48:27,560
What is it?

1765
01:48:27,800 --> 01:48:31,240
Where's Riggs? I didn't know
he could hold his breath that long.

1766
01:48:31,480 --> 01:48:32,960
I'm taking a bath, Leo.

1767
01:48:33,200 --> 01:48:37,200
I can see that. And it's cold water, too.
There goes your image.

1768
01:48:37,440 --> 01:48:38,920
Listen, I got great news.

1769
01:48:39,160 --> 01:48:41,840
Once again, Leo Getz has delivered.

1770
01:48:42,080 --> 01:48:44,520
Okay, I have sold this turkey.

1771
01:48:44,760 --> 01:48:48,920
This termite-infested dump is now gone.
Okay?

1772
01:48:49,160 --> 01:48:52,880
All you have to do is sign the contract
before the suckers change their mind.

1773
01:48:53,120 --> 01:48:55,160
Okay? I did it!

1774
01:48:55,400 --> 01:48:56,800
The house is off the market.

1775
01:48:57,040 --> 01:49:00,600
We're gonna stay in this "termite-infested turkey"
for another ten years.

1776
01:49:00,840 --> 01:49:03,720
- At least.
- Maybe I'll get married here.

1777
01:49:03,960 --> 01:49:05,720
- Come on, out.
- You can't do this.

1778
01:49:05,960 --> 01:49:08,520
- Out.
- No, you can't do that.

1779
01:49:08,760 --> 01:49:11,320
You can't do that. I have contracts signed.

1780
01:49:11,560 --> 01:49:13,720
Because we're partners,
no commission. Okay?

1781
01:49:13,960 --> 01:49:14,640
Partners?

1782
01:49:14,880 --> 01:49:16,960
You and Riggs owe me two new tires.

1783
01:49:17,200 --> 01:49:17,960
Why?

1784
01:49:18,200 --> 01:49:21,200
Because bullets aren't covered
in normal road hazard. That's why!

1785
01:49:21,440 --> 01:49:23,360
I want those tires. No conditions.

1786
01:49:23,600 --> 01:49:24,880
Leo, get out of here!

1787
01:49:25,120 --> 01:49:27,080
- Don't tell me to get out!
- Out!

1788
01:49:27,320 --> 01:49:31,520
Okay, I'm going.
You're lucky your wife's here.

1789
01:49:33,720 --> 01:49:35,120
Don't come crying to me if...

1790
01:49:35,360 --> 01:49:36,040
Get out!

1791
01:49:36,280 --> 01:49:40,400
- Termites get...
- No more!

1792
01:49:41,360 --> 01:49:44,080
Your friends.

1793
01:49:44,440 --> 01:49:48,240
Ten more years till forced retirement.

1794
01:49:48,280 --> 01:49:52,360
That's 3,650 days.

1795
01:49:52,600 --> 01:49:55,880
- Forty-nine.
- Oh, yeah.

1796
01:50:05,560 --> 01:50:08,960
I gotta improve my image.

1797
01:50:18,560 --> 01:50:21,360
'Bye, Daddy!

1798
01:50:22,360 --> 01:50:25,080
'Bye, baby.

1799
01:50:32,520 --> 01:50:34,560
What are you smiling at?

1800
01:50:34,800 --> 01:50:36,320
Why weren't you at my party?

1801
01:50:36,560 --> 01:50:38,120
I knew you weren't going to retire.

1802
01:50:38,360 --> 01:50:42,000
I've been wrong about a few things
in my life, but I knew you wouldn't retire.

1803
01:50:42,240 --> 01:50:44,040
Well, I knew you couldn't stop smoking.

1804
01:50:44,280 --> 01:50:46,720
I'm smoking to forget
my dog-biscuit problem.

1805
01:50:46,960 --> 01:50:48,560
What dog-biscuit problem?

1806
01:50:48,800 --> 01:50:50,560
I've been chasing more cars lately...

1807
01:50:50,800 --> 01:50:53,920
...and when I try to lick my balls,
I keep falling off the couch.

1808
01:50:54,160 --> 01:50:55,280
Jesus Christ.

1809
01:50:55,520 --> 01:50:56,920
I'm driving. Other side.

1810
01:50:57,160 --> 01:51:00,040
I've got no dispute. I just came over
to open the door for you.

1811
01:51:00,280 --> 01:51:01,480
Thank you for opening it.

1812
01:51:01,720 --> 01:51:04,200
An old fella like you
needs all the help he can get.

1813
01:51:04,440 --> 01:51:05,480
I'll show you.

1814
01:51:05,720 --> 01:51:08,480
- Who's a grumpy bastard?
- I'm a grumpy bastard.

1815
01:51:08,720 --> 01:51:10,000
- You know something?
- What?

1816
01:51:10,240 --> 01:51:13,880
When I do retire,
I hope your next partner is just like you.

1817
01:51:14,120 --> 01:51:17,760
There's winners and there's losers,
and God wouldn't do that to me.

1818
01:51:18,000 --> 01:51:19,800
He did it to me.

1819
01:51:20,040 --> 01:51:22,080
I know.

1820
01:51:22,320 --> 01:51:25,120
See what I mean?

1821
01:51:25,560 --> 01:51:26,840
My point exactly.

1822
01:51:27,080 --> 01:51:29,960
Son of a bitch!

1823
01:51:31,920 --> 01:51:33,240
Stay away from my daughter!

1824
01:51:33,480 --> 01:51:35,720
You can't be serious?
What are you talking about?

1825
01:51:35,960 --> 01:51:37,240
I saw you kiss Rianne.

1826
01:51:37,480 --> 01:51:39,520
She kissed me. She finds me irresistible.

1827
01:51:39,760 --> 01:51:42,560
- That's not the point!
- It was a platonic peck on the cheek.

1828
01:51:42,800 --> 01:51:45,240
If it's just friendship,
try shaking hands next time.

1829
01:51:45,480 --> 01:51:48,760
- Are you getting enough fiber in your diet?
- I'm getting enough fiber!

1830
01:51:49,000 --> 01:51:50,080
I'm spoken for, okay?

1831
01:51:50,320 --> 01:51:53,040
I'm gonna pick Lorna up
from the hospital this afternoon.

1832
01:51:53,280 --> 01:51:54,480
We're practically...

1833
01:51:54,720 --> 01:51:57,000
- You're serious?
- We've got a dog and everything.

1834
01:51:57,240 --> 01:51:59,440
I figure I can make ends meet.

1835
01:51:59,680 --> 01:52:04,600
